<font color="#FF0000">SAY WHAT YOU MEAN!</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 20 22:02:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Some of you may have noticed my sometimes inapproriate attempts at humor.  My jabs at Cook..Silent Warrior.. Chet... Professor... et al, even my silly sparring with Doc Spatz... may lead some to think that I am a light hearted person... not very serious... unsensitive or simply have shit for brains.<br>
Could be that the smoke cloud laid down is not for you but for me.  Maybe I am trying to convince myself that life is just a big joke!  I wonder if laughing is really upside down crying.  Do I laugh to keep from crying?<br>
Some very graphic, vague, crude, sophisticated, foolish and intelligent discourse occurs on this site.  It is painful to read.  Do I make jest because I am sad?<br>
Am I so desperatly seeking acceptance that I scramble for common ground too quickly... as I did when I offended Doc Del with my overzealous ministrations of new friendship?<br>
Do I, like others, over react in loving the enemy... in hating the enemy?<br>
I have killed a lot of children, women and men.  Can I undo the pain by perpetuating hate for the &quot;enemy&quot;... or lay in a blubbering heap on the bar room floor begging forgiveness?&quot; Neither method works...for me!<br>
All that holds me together is that complicated laundry list of beliefs and values somewhere inside my heart.  When I become concerned with their validity I stand on a soap box and enlist common believers... when my shakiest values are attacked, I get tunnel vision and go for the academic throat.  Fear dictates that I must not lose another battle. Sometimes, in the moments of greatest confusion, I imitate my father and grandfathers... in a rote fashion.  I guess we call that culture or tradition... am I a prisoner of past thinking on the part of other men?  My Dad didn't do everything right... just most of it!<br>
Out of rockets and 40 mike mike... linked ammo is all gone...crew members all WIA and KIA... weather's bad... running low on fuel... Guess I need to land somewhere.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
